obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (42557)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42557&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Maintenance Orders Enforcement Act, 1921.`
  line
  line `^1(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*].]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid.,for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "except Part B States".`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (42558)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42558&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `"Court of summary jurisdiction" means the Court of a Chief Presidency Magistrate or of a District`
  line Magistrate;
  line
  line `"dependants" means such persons as a person against whom a maintenance order is made is liable to`
  line `maintain according to the law in force in ^1`
  line `[the reciprocating territory] in which the maintenance order is`
  line made;
  line
  line `^2["India" means the territory of India excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir*;]`
  line
  line `"maintenance order" means a decree or order, other than an order of affiliation, made by a Court in`
  line `the exercise of civil or criminal jurisdiction for the periodical payment of sums of money towards the`
  line `maintenance of the wife or other dependants of the person against whom the order is made;`
  line
  line `"prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `"proper authority" means the authority appointed by, or under the law of, a reciprocating territory to`
  line `receive and transmit documents to which this Act applies; and`
  line
  line `^3["reciprocating territory" means any country or territory outside India in respect of which this Act for`
  line `the time being applies by virtue of a declaration under section 3.]`
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1952, s. 3, for "the Part of His Majesty's Dominions".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 47 of 1952, s. 3, for definition of "reciprocating territory".`
  line
  line `4. Definition of "States" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule. Earlier it was inserted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (42559)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Declaration of reciprocal arrangements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1952, s. 4, for section 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42559&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Declaration of reciprocal arrangements.—If the Central Government is satisfied that`
  line `legal provision exists in any country or territory outside India for the enforcement within that`
  line `country or territory of maintenance orders made by Courts in India, the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that this Act applies in respect of that country or`
  line `territory and thereupon it shall apply accordingly.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42560)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Registration in India of maintenance orders maintenance orders made in the reciprocating territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42560&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Where a maintenance order has, whether before or after the passing of this Act, been made against`
  line `any person by any Court in any reciprocating territory, and a certified copy of the order has been`
  line `transmitted by the proper authority of that territory to the Central Government, the Central`
  line `Government shall send a copy of the order to the prescribed officer of a Court in ^1`
  line `[India] for`
  line `registration, and, on receipt thereof, the order shall be registered in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court in which an order is to be so registered as aforesaid shall, if the Court by which`
  line `the order was made was, in the opinion of the Central Government, a Court of superior jurisdiction,`
  line `be a High Court, and, if the Court was not, in its opinion, a Court of superior jurisdiction, be a`
  line `Court of summary jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (42561)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Transmission of maintenance orders made in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42561&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Where a Court in ^1`
  line `[India] has,`
  line `whether before or after the commencement of this Act, made a maintenance order against any`
  line `person, and it is proved to that Court that the person against whom the order was made is resident`
  line `in a reciprocating territory, the Court shall send to the Central Government, for transmission to the`
  line `proper authority of that territory, a certified copy of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (42562)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power of summary Courts to make provisional maintenance order against persons resident in reciprocating territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42562&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where application is made to a Court of summary`
  line `jurisdiction in ^1`
  line `[India] for a maintenance order against any person, and it is proved that that person`
  line `is resident in a reciprocating territory, the Court may, in the absence of that person, if after hearing`
  line `the evidence it is satisfied of the justice of the application, make any such order as it might have`
  line `made if that person had wilfully neglected to attend the Court; but in such case the order shall be`
  line `provisional only and shall have no effect unless and until confirmed by a competent Court in such`
  line territory.
  line
  line `(2) The evidence of every witness who is examined on any such application shall be reduced to`
  line `writing, and such deposition shall be read over to, and signed by, him.`
  line
  line `(3) Where such an order is made, the Court shall send to the Central Government, for`
  line `transmission to the proper authority of the reciprocating territory in which the person against whom`
  line `the order is made is alleged to reside, the depositions so taken and a certified copy of the order`
  line `together with a statement of the grounds on which the making of the order might have been`
  line `opposed if the person against whom the order is made had been duly served with a summons and`
  line `had appeared at the hearing and such information as the Court possesses for facilitating the`
  line `identification of that person and ascertaining his whereabouts.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any such provisional order has come before a Court in a reciprocating territory for`
  line `confirmation, and the order has by that Court been remitted to the Court of summary jurisdiction`
  line `which made the order for the purpose of taking further evidence, that Court shall, after giving the`
  line `prescribed notice, proceed to take the evidence in like manner and subject to the like conditions as`
  line `the evidence in support of the original application.`
  line
  line `(5) If it appears to the Court hearing such evidence that the order ought not to have been made,`
  line `the Court may rescind the order, but in any other case the depositions shall be sent to the Central`
  line `Government and dealt with in like manner as the original depositions.`
  line
  line `(6) The confirmation of an order made under this section shall not affect any power of a Court`
  line `of summary jurisdiction to vary or rescind that order:`
  line
  line `Provided that, on the making of a varying or rescinding order, the Court shall send a certified`
  line `copy thereof to the Central Government for transmission to the proper authority of the reciprocating`
  line `territory in which the original order was confirmed, or to which it was sent for confirmation and`
  line `that, in the case of an order varying the original order, the order shall not have any effect unless and`
  line `until confirmed in like manner as the original order.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (42563)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers of Court of summary jurisdiction to confirm maintenance order made out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42563&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a maintenance order has been made by a Court in a reciprocating territory and`
  line `the order is provisional only, and has no effect unless and until confirmed by a Court of summary`
  line `jurisdiction in ^1`
  line `[India], and a certified copy of the order, together with the depositions of the`
  line `witnesses and a statement of the grounds on which the order might have been opposed, has been`
  line `transmitted to the Central Government, and it appears to the Central Government that the person`
  line `against whom the order has been made is resident in ^1`
  line `[India], the Central Government may send the`
  line `said documents to the prescribed officer of a Court of summary jurisdiction, with a requisition that`
  line `a summons be issued calling upon the person to show cause why that order should not be`
  line `confirmed, and, upon receipt of such documents and requisition, the Court shall issue such a`
  line `summons and cause it to be served upon such person.`
  line
  line `(2) A summons issued under sub-section (1) shall for all purposes be deemed to be a summons`
  line `issued by the Court in the exercise of its original criminal jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) At the hearing it shall be open to the person to whom the summons was issued to raise any`
  line `defence which he might have raised in the original proceedings had he been a party thereto, but no`
  line `other defence, and the certificate from the Court which made the provisional order stating the`
  line `grounds on which the making of the order might have been opposed if the person against whom the`
  line `order was made had been a party to the proceedings shall be conclusive evidence that those grounds`
  line `are grounds on which objection may be taken.`
  line
  line `(4) If at the hearing the person served with the summons does not appear or, on appearing, fails`
  line `to satisfy the Court that the order ought not to be confirmed, the Court may, notwithstanding any`
  line `pecuniary limit imposed on its power by any law for the time being in force in ^1`
  line `[India], confirm the`
  line `order either without modification or with such modifications as to the Court after hearing the`
  line `evidence may seem just:`
  line
  line `Provided that no sum shall be awarded as maintenance under this section, or shall be`
  line `recoverable as such, at a rate exceeding that proposed in the provisional order.`
  line
  line `(5) If the person to whom the summons was issued appears at the hearing and satisfies the`
  line `Court that for the purpose of any defence it is necessary to remit the case to the Court which made`
  line `the provisional order for the taking of any further evidence, the Court may for that purpose send a`
  line `certified copy of the record to the Central Government for transmission to that Court through the`
  line `proper authority of the reciprocating territory, and may adjourn the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a provisional order has been confirmed under this section, it may be varied for`
  line `rescinded in like manner as if it had originally been made by the confirming Court, and where on an`
  line `application for rescission or variation the Court is satisfied that it is necessary to remit the case to`
  line `the Court which made the provisional order for the purpose of taking any further evidence, the`
  line `Court may for that purpose send a certified copy of the record to the Central Government for`
  line `transmission to that Court through the proper authority of the reciprocating territory, and may`
  line `adjourn the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (42564)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Enforcement of maintenance orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42564&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, where an`
  line `order has been registered under this Act in a High Court, the order shall, from the date of such`
  line `registration, be of the same force and effect, and all proceedings may be taken thereon as if it had`
  line `been an order originally obtained in the High Court in the exercise of its civil jurisdiction, or in`
  line `such Civil Court subordinate to that High Court as may be named by the High Court in this behalf,`
  line `and that Court shall have power to enforce the order accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A Court of summary jurisdiction in which an order has been registered under this Act or by`
  line `which an order has been confirmed under this Act, and the officers of such Court, shall have such`
  line `powers and perform such duties, for the purpose of enforcing the order, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (42565)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment of charges for transmission of sums awarded as maintenance and other costs and charges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42565&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A Court in registering or confirming an order for maintenance in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act shall direct that the charges for the transmission to the Court, from which`
  line `the order has been received or in which the provisional order has been made, as the case may be, of`
  line `the sum awarded as maintenance shall be borne by the person against whom the order has been so`
  line `made or confirmed, and shall be recovered from him in addition to the sum awarded as maintenance`
  line `and in addition to, and in the same manner as, such other costs and charges as may be awarded or`
  line `levied by the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42566)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Proof of documents signed by officers of Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the States".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42566&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act, any`
  line `document purporting to be signed by a judge or officer of a Court outside ^1`
  line `[India] shall, until the`
  line `contrary is proved, be deemed to have been so signed without proof of the signature of judicial or`
  line `official character of the person appearing to have signed it, and the officerof a Court by whom a`
  line `document is signed shall, until the contrary is provided, be deemed to have been the proper officer`
  line `of the Court to sign the document.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (42567)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Depositions to be evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42567&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Depositions taken in a Court in any reciprocating territory`
  line `may, for the purposes of this Act, be received in evidence in proceedings before Courts of summary`
  line `jurisdiction under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (42568)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Rule-making power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158&sectionId=42568&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_000010_192118_1523344048158
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] The Central Government ^2`
  line `[may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules^3]`
  line `for the purpose of carrying into effect the purposes of this Act, and in`
  line `particular may make rules for the levy of the costs or charges for anything done under this Act and`
  line `for all matters which are directed or permitted to be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should`
  line `not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as`
  line `the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to`
  line `the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section12, renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for "may make rules" (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
  line
  line `3. For such rules, see Gazette of India, 1923, Pt. I, p. 1263.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
